Form990ScheduleCPartIV.ReturnReference: Organizations Direct and Indirect Political Campaign Activities:
Form990ScheduleCPartIV.Explanation: The organization meets with local legislators and travels to the state capitol to meet with state legislators. At its discretion, the organization gives directly to various political campaigns. On occasion the organization holds receptions for political candidates.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, line 6
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Builder membership - person who is, or has been, in the business of building or rebuilding homes, apartments, schools, commercial, industrial or other structures normally related to a community, or in land development, within the jurisdiction of the organization; who shall agree to abide by the provisions of the bylaws (and any amendments), and shall subscribe to the Code of Ethics Associate membership - person engaged in any allied trade, industry, business or profession within the territorial jurisdiction of the organization Affiliate membership - person employed with a firm or corporation, one employee of which is already a Builder or Associate member holding membership in the National Association of Home Builders Honorary Life membership - may be extended by the Board of Directors in its discretion to any Builder or Associate member who is 65 years of age or older, during his current membership year provided he has been a member in good standing for at least ten years immediately prior to the end of his current membership year and has reduced his business activity to such an extent as to be considered partially or fully retired. An Honorary Life Member shall be entitled to all privileges of the Wichita Area Builders Association membership as pertains to a Builder or Associate member, on a dues free basis, except he may not hold an elected office. An Honorary Life member may elect to continue his association with the National Association of Home Builders upon payment of the required dues. Associate Council membership - person employed with a firm or corporation, one employee of which is already an Associate member holding membership in the National Association of Home Builders

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15a
